    </div>

    <!-- Splash
    ================================================== -->
    <div id="myCarousel" class="carousel slide" data-ride="carousel">
      <div id="home" class="carousel-inner">
        <div class="item active">
          <!-- <img alt="Background" src="/assets/background.png" style="size: 100% auto"/> -->
          <div class="container">
            <div class="carousel-caption">
              <h1 class="steven">Steven Fleming Jr</h1>
              <h2>Full-Stack Web Developer</h2>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
    </div>



    <!-- Skills
    ================================================== -->
    <!-- Wrap the rest of the page in another container to center all the content. -->

    <div class="container marketing">

      <!-- Three columns of text below the carousel -->
      <div class="row" id="skills">
        <h1 class="text-muted skills" >Skills</h1>
        <p class="lead" style="text-align: center">This is what I can do.</p>
        <div class="col-lg-4">
          <!-- <img alt="Picture" class="img-circle" height="140" image-url='full-bars.png' width="140" /> -->
          <%= image_tag "full-bars.png", :class => "img-circle", :height => "140", :width => "140" %>
          <h2>Very Comfortable</h2>
            <li>Ruby</li>
            <li>Rails</li>
            <li>HTML5</li>
            <li>CSS3</li>
            <li>Javascript</li>
            <li>JQuery</li>
            <li>Bootstrap</li>
            <li>PostgreSQL</li>
            <li>Paper Prototyping</li>
        </div><!-- /.col-lg-4 -->
        <div class="col-lg-4">
          <img alt="Picture" class="img-circle" height="140" src="/assets/half-bars.png" width="140" />
          <h2>Learning</h2>
            <li>Objective-C</li>
            <li>Knockout.js</li>
            <li>Node.js</li>
        </div><!-- /.col-lg-4 -->
        <div class="col-lg-4">
          <img alt="Picture" class="img-circle" height="140" src="/assets/empty-bars.png" width="140" />
          <h2>Want to learn</h2>
            <li>RubyMotion</li>
            <li>MongoDB</li>
            <li>Eclipse</li>
            <li>Angular.js</li>
            <li>MySQL Workbench</li>
            <li>Cucumber</li>
            <li>RSpec</li>
            <li>TDD</li>
            <li>BDD</li>
        </div><!-- /.col-lg-4 -->
      </div><!-- /.row -->


      <!-- Portfolio -->

      <hr class="featurette-divider">

      <div class="row featurette" id="portfolio">
        <div class="col-md-7">
          <h1 class="featurette-heading text-muted">Portfolio</h1>
          <p class="lead">These are the things that I build<br><strong>Stee.vn built using Ruby on Rails, PostgreSQL, HTML5, CSS3, jQuery, LocalScroll, and Bootstrap.</strong></p>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-5">
          <a target="_blank" href="" ><img class="featurette-image img-responsive project" src="/assets/placeholder.png" alt="stee.vn"></a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="row featurette move">
        <div class="col-md-5 one">
          <a target="_blank" href="http://glacial-badlands-4316.heroku.com"><img class="featurette-image img-responsive project" src="/assets/counting.png" atl="Counting Application"></a>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-7 two">
          <h1 class="featurette-heading text-muted">Counting Application</h1>
          <p class="lead">My spin on the "Fizz Buzz" challenge. Add and subtract your own custom variables from the list of numbers.<br><strong>Built with Ruby on Rails, PostgreSQL, HTML5, CSS3, and Bootstrap.</strong></p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="row featurette">
        <div class="col-md-7">
          <h1 class="featurette-heading text-muted">Subway Roulette</h1>
          <p class="lead">Generates random Subway Sub ingredient combinations. Challenge yourself to eat one, but be careful!<br><strong>Built with Ruby on Rails, PostgreSQL, HTML5, and CSS3.</strong></p>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-5">
          <a target="_blank" href=""><img class="featurette-image img-responsive project" src="/assets/subway.png" atl="Subway Roulette"></a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="row featurette move">
        <div class="col-md-5 one">
          <a target="_blank" href=""><img class="featurette-image img-responsive project" src="/assets/senior_nav.png" atl="seniornavigator.org"></a>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-7 two">
          <h1 class="featurette-heading text-muted">Senior Navigator</h1>
          <p class="lead">Built during Capital One's Creating 4 Communities Hackathon, an event aimed at helping small Non-Profits migrate existing static HTML/PHP websites to more manageable CMS based websites. I was responsible for building the "feature image scroller", a "sponsor carousel", and two dynamically updating pages of the site.<br><strong>Built with Wordpress, Various WP Plugins, HTML5 and CSS3.</strong></p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <hr class="featurette-divider">
      <!-- About -->
      <div class="row featurette" id="about">
        <div class="col-md-5">
          <img class="featurette-image img-responsive" src="/assets/walking.png" alt="Steven Fleming">
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-7">
          <h1 class="featurette-heading text-muted">Who am I?</h1>
          <p class="lead bold">There is a lot of stuff to know about me...</p>
          <p>That being said I was born and raised in Arlington, Virginia and spent most of my life here enjoying everything the DC Area has to offer.  Eventually I went to Prep School in Connecticut and then I moved to Walla Walla, Washington where I got a Bachelors Degree in Geology.<br> 
          After graduation I spent the next 3 years as a consultant traveling the United States visiting various colleges and universities working to improve their Greek Systems. I visited UGA, U of Montana, UCLA, UCI, Syracuse and Northeastern University among a bunch of other schools.<br>
          Today I find myself once again back in Arlington living with my beautiful girlfriend and spending all of my free time working on various programming projects. My goals right now are to work on exciting projects, solve super hard problems, and to stay on top of all the new technologies in the Web Development world.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div><!-- /.container -->
